{
  "stem": "23438.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I told my mother I'm going to France.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Mother wasn't very happy about it, but she couldn't really stop me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She had, in the meantime, met someone who told us that he knew my father and my brother in Wilno, that they were shipped to a concentration camp in Stutthoff, wherever that was, somewhere on the Baltic Sea, that he knew that my father had been killed there.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He didn't know-- he wasn't sure about my brother, that my brother had given his identity as half-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He couldn't say he was fully Aryan, because he was with a father who was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And my mother understood from there that he had been killed also.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I don't think it ever-- it ever reconciled herself to the fact that she'd let him go.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She felt she could have saved him if he was there with us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Anyway, she let me go, unhappily, but she did let me go.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "She gave me $50 that she must have left from the money that had been distributed around during the occupation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I met in Lodz a young man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "His name was Abrasza Zemsz, who came from Paris on the repatriation train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was a train shuttling through Europe from east to west and from west to east, carrying refugees wherever they wanted to go.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they brought a number of people from Germany back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Then they were going back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And something like, oh, a dozen people loaded onto the train to go back with them, to go to France, to go to the west.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I was one of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I don't remember how we parlayed our way through the Polish border.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
